<br>
The aliens pulled Harper up and out of the cell he shared with Dylan. The door was closed behind him and he was pushed forwards. One of the three aliens undid his handcuffs and pushed him forward again. Trance had no idea what species they were, and she found that she really didn’t care. Her eyes were fixed on Harper as they pushed him towards the torture bench. His eyes widened in horror, Harper had seen one of these before and in an instant, Trance knew there wasn’t a chance in hell that he was going to let himself be put on one again.<br>
<br>
Suddenly, with more speed anyone had seen in him before, a speed born of desperation, Harper’s elbow flicked back catching the alien behind him directly in the nose. As the alien stumbled back, Harper grabbed his gun and turned to face the other two. He got off one shot before two volleys of fire hit him in the torso and upper thigh. He turned sideways, his eyes loosing focus. He slowly sank to his knees, looking in disbelief at the blood staining his shirt. Slowly he looked up and into Trance’s eyes, now wide with shock.<br>
<br>
‘Trance…..’<br>
<br>
Harper sank to the floor and his chest shuddered, sank…and although the 2 humans, Nietzschean, Magog and pixie all willed it to rise again, it never would.<br>
<br>
